article.headline: Jacksonville St. 70, SE Missouri 67
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Will Ginn hit a 30-foot basket with 0.5 seconds left in the game to give Jacksonville State a 70-67 win over Southeast Missouri State on Sunday. Southeast Missouri (3-8, 1-2 Ohio Valley) had tied it at 67 when Brandon Foust tipped in a missed shot with 5 seconds left. Ginn got the ball on the ensuing inbounds pass and put up the game-winning 3-pointer. Ginn finished with eight points for Jacksonville State (3-6, 1-2). The Gamecocks had five players in double figures, led by Dorien Brown with 15 and Courtney Bradley with 12. Jacksonville State led throughout the first half for a 39-30 lead at the break. But the Redhawks opened the second half with a 20-8 run before tying it 50-50, then tied it on a free throw by Foust with 10:25 remaining. A layup on the next possession gave Southeast Missouri its first lead of the game. The Gamecocks regained the lead at 67-65 on Bradley's layup with 1:09 to play. Michael Rembert led Southeast Missouri with 20 points, and Foust added 12. Bradley had 12 rebounds to go with his 12 points for Jacksonville State. Erik Adams also had a double-double, finishing with 11 points and 11 rebounds.
